Episodes.Title: Herrenvolk (2)
Episodes.Plot: Jeremiah Smith and Mulder are on the run from the alien bounty hunter, and Smith takes Mulder to a small farm tended to by identical sets of children, and all the girls are clones of his sister when she was still a child. Mulder prepares to take Jeremiah and one of the clones to see his mother in the hospital, but the bounty hunter catches up with them. Meanwhile, the Syndicate suspects that they have a traitor in their midst and plan a trap which results in X being executed by the Cigarette-Smo
Episodes.GuestStars: Brian Thompson, Garvin Cross, Ken Camroux, Vanessa Morley, Roy Thinnes, Casey Murphy, Sean Murphy

Episodes.Title: Home
Episodes.Plot: A baby is found buried alive in shallow ground and appears to have birth defects resulting from generations of inbreeding, leading Mulder and Scully to a reclusive family who have a history of inbred children.
Episodes.GuestStars: Tucker Smallwood, Sebastian Spence, Chris Norris, John Trottier, Karin Konoval, Judith Maxie, Kenny James, Lachlan Murdoch, Neil Denis, Cory Frye, Douglas Smith, Adrian Hughes

Episodes.Title: Teliko
Episodes.Plot: After several African-American men are killed and the color is drained from their skin, Mulder learns about the Teliko, an African folktale about a creature who must suck the pigmentation from a persons body in order to survive.
Episodes.GuestStars: Maxine Guess, Michael O'Shea, Don Stewart, Geoffrey Aye-Bonte, Dexter Bell, Carl Lumbly, Willie Amakye, Zakes Mokae, Bob Morrisey

Episodes.Title: Unruhe
Episodes.Plot: Several kidnappings of young women linked by distorted photographs lead Mulder and Scully to a man who can imprint his darkest fantasies onto undeveloped film and is trying to save the women from the "Howlers".
Episodes.GuestStars: Pruitt Taylor Vince, William MacDonald, Walter Marsh, Sharon Alexander, Ron Chartier, Michael Cram, Christopher Royal, Michele Melland, Scott Heindl, Angela Donahue

Episodes.Title: The Field Where I Died
Episodes.Plot: After an FBI raid on a doomsday cult called the "Temple of the Seven Stars", Mulder meets Melissa, a cultist who claims to have known him in a previous life during the American Civil War. Scully believes the woman is a delusional schizophrenic, but Mulder allows himself to be drawn into her fantasies.
Episodes.GuestStars: Donna White, Doug Abrahams, Anthony Harrison, Michael Dobson, Les Gallagher, Douglas Roy Dack, Kristen Cloke, Michael Massee

Episodes.Title: Sanguinarium
Episodes.Plot: A link to the four witches Sabbaths is found after a doctor loses control and kills a patient on the operating table, and Mulder suspects a nurse may be practicing witchcraft.
Episodes.GuestStars: O-Lan Jones, Richard Beymer, Arlene Mazerolle, Gregory Thirloway, John Juliani, Martin Evans, Paul Raskin, Andrew Airlie, Marie Stillin, Norman Armour, Nancy J. Lilley, Celine Lockhart, Nina Roman

Episodes.Title: Musings of a Cigarette Smoking Man
Episodes.Plot: Frohike pieces together and recites to Mulder and Scully what could be the possible life story of the Cigarette Smoking Man; from a young captain in the U.S. Army recruited to assassinate President Kennedy, to becoming the mysterious man in the shadows at the height of a global conspiracy. What measures will the Cigarette Smoking Man take to ensure that he remains a mystery forever?
Episodes.GuestStars: Paul Jarrett, Dan Zukovic, Peter Hanlon, Dean Aylesworth, David Fredericks, Laurie Murdoch, Michael St. John Smith, Marc Baur, Jude Zachary, Gonzalo Canton, Steve Oatway, Colin Lawrence, Anthony Ashbee, Pete Mele

Episodes.Title: Tunguska (1)
Episodes.Plot: A rock sample taken from Mars is intercepted at an airport and infects a security officer with the Black Cancer, while Mulder is given a tip about potentially dangerous paramilitary operations but is doubtful when the informant turns out to be Alex Krycek.   Reluctantly, Mulder accepts Krycek's help and tracks the rock to Russia where he discovers an elaborate test being performed by Russian scientists.
Episodes.GuestStars: Malcolm Stewart, David Bloom, Campbell Lane, Stefan Arngrim, Brent Stait, Fritz Weaver

Episodes.Title: Terma (2)
Episodes.Plot: While imprisoned in Russia and infected with the Black Cancer, Mulder learns that Krycek is working with the men responsible and everything has been a setup from the start, while Scully and Skinner are called to a suspicious Senate hearing where the only question is the whereabouts of Agent Mulder.
Episodes.GuestStars: Jessica Schreier, Brent Stait, Malcolm Stewart, Campbell Lane, Robin Mossley, Brenda McDonald, Pamela MacDonald, Eileen Pedde, Stefan Arngrim, Jan Rube?, Fritz Weaver

Episodes.Title: Paper Hearts
Episodes.Plot: Mulder's dreams help him in finding the body of a little girl which reopens one of his old cases in the Violent Crimes Unit and leads him to believe the killer he captured had more victims and may have taken his sister many years before.
Episodes.GuestStars: Vanessa Morley, Byrne Piven, Jane Perry, Edward Diaz, Paul Bittante, Carly McKillip, Tom Noonan, Jenny-Lynn Hutcheson

Episodes.Title: El Mundo Gira
Episodes.Plot: A strange yellow rain kills a migrant girl, and her family believes that a mythical creature was the cause and has manifested itself inside the brother of her fiancé, who has since disappeared.
Episodes.GuestStars: Pamela Diaz, Susan Bain, Robert Thurston, Michael Kopsa, Markus Hondro, Janeth Munoz, Fabricio Santin, Jose Vargus, Tony Dean Smith, Rubén Blades, Raymond Cruz, Jose Yenque, Simi, Lillian Hurst

Episodes.Title: Leonard Betts
Episodes.Plot: After the body of a decapitated EMT disappears from the morgue and an identical man starts work at the same hospital, Mulder believes that the man has the ability to regrow parts of his body, including his head. The agents soon discover that Betts' body is riddled with cancer and he is able to live in that condition but needs to feed on cancerous tumors to keep up his strength.
Episodes.Writer: Frank Spotnitz, Vince Gilligan, John Shiban
Episodes.GuestStars: Paul McCrane, Jennifer Clement, Marjorie Lovett, Sean Campbell, David Hurtubise, Peter Bryant, Laara Sadiq, J. Douglas Stewart, Lucia Walters, Ken Jones, Greg Newmeyer, Don Ackerman, Brad Loree

Episodes.Title: Never Again
Episodes.Plot: While Mulder is forced to take a vacation he leaves Scully with an assignment to keep her busy until he returns. However, she decides to start living and goes on a date with a man who believes that his tattoo talks to him and is telling him to stay away from other women.
Episodes.GuestStars: Rodney Rowland, Jodie Foster, Bill Croft, Jay Donohue, B.J. Harrison, Jillian Fargey, Jan Bailey Mattia, Igor Morozof, Ian Robison

Episodes.Title: Memento Mori
Episodes.Plot: Scully's recent failing health is revealed to be inoperable brain cancer, which is common among abductees. She meets with other abductees with the same condition and forms a special bond with a dying woman, while Mulder tries to save her from a doctor who may be connected with the abductions.
Episodes.Writer: Chris Carter, Vince Gilligan, John Shiban, Frank Spot
Episodes.GuestStars: Sean Allen, Julie Bond, David Lovgren, Gillian Barber, Casey Murphy

Episodes.Title: Kaddish
Episodes.Plot: Issac Luria, a Jewish man, is killed by a group of teenagers working for a racist shop owner, but one of them is soon strangled to death, and the fingerprints on his neck are from Issac. Despite other factors, Mulder becomes convinced that the man has returned from the dead to exact revenge.
Episodes.GuestStars: Justine Miceli, David Groh, Harrison Coe, Jabin Litwiniec, David Wohl, Jonathan Whittaker, Timur Karabilgin, George Gordon, Murrey Rabinovitch, David Freeman, Channon Roe

Episodes.Title: Unrequited
Episodes.Plot: When a U.S. military general is inexplicably murdered in the back of his limousine, a paramilitary group is suspected. They believe it was a soldier who they liberated from a Vietnam POW camp and is plotting to kill certain corrupt military figures.
Episodes.GuestStars: Larry Musser, Lesley Ewen, Ryan Michael, Allan Franz, Jennifer Jasey, Mark Holden, Don McWilliams, Peter LaCroix, Scott Hylands, William Taylor, William Nunn

Episodes.Title: Tempus Fugit (1)
Episodes.Plot: While celebrating Scully's 33rd birthday, a strange woman informs Mulder that NICAP member Max Fenig (see Fallen Angel) has recently died in a plane crash. After a visit to the crash site and finding Max's body with radiation burns on it, Mulder suggests that the plane was intercepted by a UFO and is rapidly being covered up by the military.
Episodes.GuestStars: Joe Spano, Tom O'Brien, Scott Bellis, Chilton Crane, Greg Michaels, Robert Moloney, Felicia Shulman, Rick Dobran, Jerry Schram, David Palffy, Mark Wilson, Marek Wiedman, Maria Luisa Cianni

Episodes.Title: Max (2)
Episodes.Plot: Mulder is arrested for investigating the plane crash and interfering with a military operation, while Scully is caught in an attempted assassination of Corporal Frish which claims the life of Agent Pendrell. Scully bails Mulder out of prison, and they go to Max Fenig's trailer to find out why he was on the plane. Mulder finds evidence of alien technology and boards a plane with it, but the plane is intercepted mid-flight and it disappears. Mulder is again left with nothing.
Episodes.GuestStars: Greg Michaels, John Destry, Rick Dobran, Jerry Schram, David Palffy, Mark Wilson, Joe Spano, Tom O'Brien, Scott Bellis, Chilton Crane

Episodes.Title: Synchrony
Episodes.Plot: A case involving a strange old man warning two scientists of events in the immediate future which come to pass (and the use of their experimental flash-freezing compound that does not exist yet) has Mulder believing that one of the scientists has come from the future to stop his own scientific breakthrough from becoming reality.
Episodes.GuestStars: Joseph Fuqua, Susan Lee Hoffman, Michael Fairman, Jed Rees, Hiro Kanagawa, Jonathan Walker, Alison Matthews, Norman Armour, Patricia Idlette, Brent Chapman, Terry Arrowsmith, Aurelio Dinunzio, Austin Basile

Episodes.Title: Small Potatoes
Episodes.Plot: Five babies in the same town are all born with tails and the local OB-GYN is blamed for tampering with fertilized eggs. However, Mulder discovers the culprit to be a simple man with a genetic deformity who may have the ability to alter his appearance.
Episodes.GuestStars: Robert Rozen, Paul McGillion, Jennifer Sterling, David Cameron, Forbes Angus, Peter Kelamis, P. Lynn Johnson, Carrie Cain Sparks, Darin Morgan, Christine Cavanaugh, Lee De Broux

Episodes.Title: Zero-Sum
Episodes.Plot: Skinner destroys evidence to cover up a woman's death and poses as Agent Mulder to complete the task. Mulder finds out about Skinner's deception and confronts him, and Skinner reveals that he is working for the Cigarette-Smoking Man in order to obtain a possible cure for Scully's cancer.
Episodes.GuestStars: Lisa Stewart, Nicolle Nattrass, Fred Keating, Addison Ridge, Barry Greene, Paul McLean, Allan Gray, Christopher J. Newton, Sterling McKay

Episodes.Title: Elegy
Episodes.Plot: After a man sees a woman trapped inside a bowling alley pin setter, he goes for help and finds police standing next to a body of the same woman. Mulder and Scully join the investigation and follow up this lead which the police won't bother with, and they are led to a mentally challenged man who works at the bowling alley.
Episodes.GuestStars: Stephen M. Porter, Alex Bruhanski, Sydney Lassick, Nancy Fish, Daniel Kamin, Lorena Gale, Michael Puttonen, Christine Willes, Ken Tremblett, Gerry Nairn

Episodes.Title: Demons
Episodes.Plot: Mulder undergoes an experimental form of hypnotherapy to recover his memories about his sister's abduction, but the treatment has side effects including psychotic behavior, and Mulder wakes up one morning in a motel room with someone else's blood all over him.
Episodes.GuestStars: Jay Acovone, Mike Nussbaum, Chris Owens, Vanessa Morley, Andrew Johnston, Terry Jang Barclay, Eric Breker, Rebecca Harker, Shelly Adam, Dean Aylesworth, Alex Haythorne

Episodes.Title: Gethsemane (1)
Episodes.Plot: While investigating the discovery of a preserved alien body found in the mountains of Canada, Mulder is contacted by Michael Kritschgau. He tells Mulder about a government conspiracy to make people believe in aliens without question, and Mulder has been the prime target.
Episodes.GuestStars: Matthew Walker, James Sutorius, Pat Skipper, John Oliver, Steve Makaj, Nancy Kerr, Barry W. Levy, Arnie Walters, Rob Freeman, Craig Brunanski
